The paper deals with the optimization problem of determining the locations at which intelligent mobile terminals prefer to connect to a given base station rather than to others. This problem involves game theory and optimal transport theory, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), game theory (cs.GT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
